BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:medienboard-immersive-2027-r1@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T221418Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261027
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261028
SUMMARY:Deadline: Medienboard Berlin-Brandenburg: Innovative Audiovisual Co
 ntent / Immersive (2027 Round 1)
DESCRIPTION:Medienboard's Immersive strand funds the development and produc
 tion of immersive and innovative audiovisual content: virtual\, augmented 
 and mixed-reality experiences plus multi-platform and cross-media projects
 \, and it also supports festival presentation of XR and innovative audiovi
 sual work. This is the most directly creative-technology-facing German reg
 ional fund open to organisations. The applicant must be a developer or ind
 ependent producer with a registered company seat in Berlin-Brandenburg or 
 elsewhere in Germany\, which rules out individual artists without a compan
 y\; international partners can participate as co-producers but cannot lead
 . THE PROCESS IS GATED: applicants submit a one-page project summary rough
 ly six weeks before the deadline\, then must hold an application meeting w
 ith a funding executive about two weeks before the deadline\, and only aft
 er that meeting is portal access granted. Plan backwards from the deadline
  accordingly. The 2026 rounds closed on 3 February\, 28 April and 21 July 
 2026\; the next live deadline is 27 October 2026\, feeding the first commi
 ttee of 2027 with decisions announced in week 5 of 2027\, a decision lag o
 f about three months. The DIGI.TALE sub-strand is restricted to students o
 f Film University Babelsberg KONRAD WOLF and DFFB.\n\nOrganisation: Medien
 board Berlin-Brandenburg GmbH\nLocation: Berlin-Brandenburg\, Germany. A B
 erlin-Brandenburg regional effect applies.\nAward: FLAG\, UNVERIFIED: amou
 nts are not stated on the public scheme page. Financial terms\, grant-vers
 us-conditionally-repayable-loan status\, own-contribution percentage and t
 he Berlin-Brandenburg regional spend requirement are set out only in the d
 ownloadable guideline PDF (Merkblatt Innovative Audiovisuelle Inhalte). No
  application fee indicated. Confirm figures and whether support is a grant
  or a repayable loan before applying.\nDuration: Project-based\; developme
 nt and production phases are funded separately.\n\nMore: https://www.medie
 nboard.de/en/funding/immersive/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_
 medium=referral
URL:https://www.medienboard.de/en/funding/immersive/?utm_source=artificialn
 ouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Berlin-Brandenburg\, Germany. A Berlin-Brandenburg regional effect
  applies.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:berlinale-talents-2027@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T221418Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260902
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260903
SUMMARY:Deadline: Berlinale Talents 2027 (Berlin International Film Festiva
 l)
DESCRIPTION:Berlinale Talents is the Berlin International Film Festival's t
 alent-development program: a week of workshops\, the Talents Lab and the T
 alent Project Market during the February 2027 Berlinale\, plus access to t
 he festival's industry network. ELIGIBILITY: international working film pr
 ofessionals with at least 1 feature\, 2 shorts\, or a widely screened or s
 treamed series\, across 15+ disciplines including directing\, sound design
 \, editing\, production\, cinematography and screenwriting. Participation 
 itself is free\; there is a EUR 15 application service fee (EUR 10 early b
 ird before 19 August 2026) and travel and accommodation are not covered. D
 eadline 2 September 2026\, 12:00 CEST. Apply via the Berlinale Talents por
 tal.\n\nOrganisation: Berlinale / Berlin International Film Festival\nLoca
 tion: Berlin\, Germany (during the Berlinale\, February 2027)\; open inter
 nationally.\nAward: Free participation in the week-long professional progr
 am (Summit workshops\, Talents Lab\, Talent Project Market\, industry netw
 orking). NO stipend\; travel and accommodation are self-covered (national 
 film institutes often fund this\; Netherlands-based filmmakers can approac
 h the Netherlands Film Fund). EUR 15 application service fee (EUR 10 early
  bird before 19 August 2026).\nDuration: One week during the Berlinale\, F
 ebruary 2027\n\nMore: https://www.berlinale-talents.de/bt/page/c/apply?utm
 _source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.berlinale-talents.de/bt/page/c/apply?utm_source=artificialn
 ouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Berlin\, Germany (during the Berlinale\, February 2027)\; open int
 ernationally.
END:VEVENT
