SUMMARY:Deadline: Berlin Senate: Arbeitsstipendien Film/Video 2027\, Kuenst
 lerinnenfoerderung (Berlin-based women artists)
DESCRIPTION:Work stipends for women film and video artists under the Berlin
  Senate's Kuenstlerinnenfoerderung (women artists' funding program). ELIGI
 BILITY: women film and video artists based in Berlin. Deadline 1 October 2
 026\, 11:00 CEST\, per the Senate's official deadline calendar. NOTE: rese
 arch-sourced from the Senate deadline calendar\; the stipend amount was no
 t published there\, so confirm details on the Senate funding pages before 
 applying.\n\nOrganisation: Berlin Senate Department for Culture and Social
  Cohesion\nLocation: Berlin\, Germany. Women film and video artists based 
 in Berlin only.\nAward: Work stipend for women film and video artists\; th
 e amount for this round is not yet confirmed (sibling Senate work stipends
  pay EUR 2\,000 per month). No application fee.\nDuration: Work stipend fo
 r 2027\n\nMore: https://www.berlin.de/sen/kultur/foerderung/antragsfristen
 /?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.berlin.de/sen/kultur/foerderung/antragsfristen/?utm_source=
 artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Berlin\, Germany. Women film and video artists based in Berlin onl
 y.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:fondazione-prada-film-fund-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T221418Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260806
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260807
SUMMARY:Deadline: Fondazione Prada Film Fund 2026
DESCRIPTION:The Fondazione Prada Film Fund is an annual initiative supporti
 ng independent cinema\, with an annual endowment of EUR 1.5 million backin
 g up to 14 feature film projects across development\, production\, and pos
 t-production. The Fund imposes NO restrictions on geography\, theme\, genr
 e\, or language and does not participate as a co-producer\, guaranteeing c
 omplete artistic freedom to filmmakers. It supports both established autho
 rs and new talents\, as well as research projects. SELECTION is based excl
 usively on quality\, originality\, vision\, and the strength and reliabili
 ty of the applicant structure\; projects are evaluated by independent read
 ers and external consultants\, with final selection and grant amounts dete
 rmined by a committee appointed by Fondazione Prada. ELIGIBILITY: applicat
 ions may be submitted only by a production company involved in the project
  (the applicant company remains solely responsible for meeting all require
 ments)\; open worldwide. DEADLINES (2026 call opened 30 June 2026): projec
 ts in production 6 August 2026\; projects in development and post-producti
 on 10 September 2026 (this card uses the earliest deadline). Post-producti
 on projects may submit a rough cut until 20 November 2026. Selected projec
 ts announced February 2027. Application documents are on the Fondazione Pr
 ada Film Fund page\; questions to filmfund@fondazioneprada.org.\n\nOrganis
 ation: Fondazione Prada\nLocation: Milan\, Italy-based fund\; open worldwi
 de to independent producers and production companies.\nAward: EUR 1.5 mill
 ion annual endowment supporting up to 14 projects. Individual grant amount
 s are set by the Fondazione Prada selection committee (no fixed per-stage 
 bands published). No application fee.\nDuration: Feature film funding (dev
 elopment\, production\, or post-production)\n\nMore: https://www.fondazion
 eprada.org/film-fund/?lang=en&utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_me
 dium=referral
URL:https://www.fondazioneprada.org/film-fund/?lang=en&utm_source=artificia
 lnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Milan\, Italy-based fund\; open worldwide to independent producers
  and production companies.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:guardian-arte-democracy-at-stake-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T221418Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260914
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260915
SUMMARY:Deadline: Democracy at Stake in Europe: Short Documentary Fund
DESCRIPTION:Guardian Documentaries and arte.tv have opened a short document
 ary film fund on the theme 'Democracy at Stake in Europe'\, supporting the
  development and production of a character-led documentary short exploring
  threats\, pressures and challenges facing democratic societies across Eur
 ope. The aim is to amplify personal stories that help audiences understand
  democracy in Europe today and to stimulate public debate\; suggested area
 s of focus include press freedom\, civic trust and democratic participatio
 n. AWARD: one project receives GBP 10\,000 in production support\; alongsi
 de the financial award\, the selected filmmaker receives editorial and cre
 ative input from the partners\, with distribution through Guardian and art
 e.tv platforms. The funding can be used for work linked to the film's deve
 lopment and production\, such as research\, filming and post-production\, 
 subject to the applicant's proposed budget and plan. ELIGIBILITY: open to 
 European filmmakers aged 18 or over\; the call is focused on a single shor
 t documentary and is intended for projects where individual experience and
  perspective are central to telling a wider story about democratic life in
  Europe. Deadline 14 September 2026.\n\nOrganisation: Guardian Documentari
 es and arte.tv\nLocation: Europe.\nAward: GBP 10\,000 in production suppor
 t for one short documentary project\, plus editorial and creative input fr
 om the partners and distribution through Guardian and arte.tv platforms.\n
 Duration: Development and production of a single short documentary.\n\nMor
 e: https://vibrantshropshire.co.uk/funding/democracy-at-stake-in-europe/?u
 tm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://vibrantshropshire.co.uk/funding/democracy-at-stake-in-europe/?u
 tm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Europe.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:circle-expanded-orbit-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T221418Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260709
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260710
SUMMARY:Deadline: CIRCLE Expanded Orbit 1st Edition
DESCRIPTION:CIRCLE Expanded Orbit is the first edition of an international 
 training programme dedicated to immersive storytelling and XR-based practi
 ces\, run by the CIRCLE Training Initiative in partnership with Onassis ON
 X. It supports women and gender-expansive filmmakers\, artists\, XR creato
 rs\, and multidisciplinary storytellers working across XR\, MR\, VR\, AR\,
  AI\, and game-based narratives\, with no prior XR experience required. Se
 lected individuals or teams of up to two receive individual mentorship\, g
 roup sessions\, co-creation workshops\, and structured feedback\, plus acc
 ess to an international network of professionals. The in-person training t
 akes place from November 21 to 26\, 2026\, in Athens\, Greece. Applicants 
 should be developing a project with a strong artistic vision and clear int
 erest in immersive formats\, ideally with a producer attached and partial 
 budget secured. A participation fee of EUR 2\,000 per person applies\, wit
 h scholarships of up to 50 percent available based on financial need.\n\nO
 rganisation: CIRCLE Training Initiative (with Onassis ONX)\nLocation: Athe
 ns\, Greece\nAward: No cash stipend. Provides individual mentorship from w
 orld-leading experts\, group sessions\, co-creation workshops\, structured
  feedback\, and access to an international professional network across fil
 m\, art\, design\, and technology. Participation fee of EUR 2\,000 per per
 son (EUR 4\,000 per team of two)\, with scholarships covering up to 50 per
 cent available for those with financial need. EUR 2\,000 participation fee
  per person (EUR 4\,000 per team of two)\; up to 50 percent scholarships a
 vailable\nDuration: 6 days (in-person training)\n\nMore: https://www.docci
 rcle.me/expanded-orbit?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=re
 ferral
URL:https://www.doccircle.me/expanded-orbit?utm_source=artificialnouveaugra
 ntdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Athens\, Greece
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:circle-fiction-orbit-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T221418Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260710
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260711
SUMMARY:Deadline: CIRCLE Fiction Orbit 3rd Edition
DESCRIPTION:CIRCLE Fiction Orbit is a one-week retreat in Herceg Novi\, Mon
 tenegro for up to six fiction feature film projects led by teams of women 
 and gender-expansive filmmakers developing their second\, third\, or fourt
 h narrative feature. Participants work with leading experts on script deve
 lopment\, legal and production strategy\, career positioning\, and receive
  psychological support throughout the creative process. Applicants must id
 entify as a woman or gender-expansive filmmaker\, work as a screenwriter\,
  director\, or producer\, have completed at least one feature\, and submit
  a project with a producer attached. Accommodation and meals are provided\
 , but travel is not covered\, and a participation fee of EUR 2\,000 per pe
 rson applies. At least one 50 percent scholarship is available annually fo
 r those with demonstrated financial need. The third edition runs October 2
 5 to November 1\, 2026\, with applications due July 10\, 2026.\n\nOrganisa
 tion: CIRCLE Training Initiative\nLocation: Herceg Novi\, Montenegro\nAwar
 d: Accommodation and meals provided\; in-depth script consultations\, lega
 l and production strategy guidance\, career development mentorship\, and p
 sychological support. Travel not covered. Participation fee of EUR 2\,000 
 per person applies. At least one 50 percent scholarship available annually
  for participants from lower-income countries\, those without national fun
 ding\, or with demonstrated financial need. EUR 2\,000 participation fee (
 accommodation and meals included\; travel not covered)\; 50 percent schola
 rship available for demonstrated need\nDuration: One week\n\nMore: https:/
 /www.doccircle.me/fiction-orbit?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_
 medium=referral
URL:https://www.doccircle.me/fiction-orbit?utm_source=artificialnouveaugran
 tdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Herceg Novi\, Montenegro
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:trace-artistic-residencies-memory-displacement-2026-27@artificialnouvea
 u.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T221418Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260618
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260619
SUMMARY:Deadline: TRACE: Artistic Residencies on Memory\, Displacement & Co
 ntemporary Europe 2026-27
DESCRIPTION:TRACE is an international artistic residency programme\, funded
  by the EU's Creative Europe programme\, exploring how contemporary art ca
 n engage with memory\, war\, displacement\, ecological crisis and the coll
 ective experiences shaping Europe today. It takes as starting points recen
 t and ongoing crises\, including the conflict in Bosnia and Herzegovina an
 d the Srebrenica genocide\, Mediterranean migration\, the ecological legac
 y of Chernobyl\, and the Russian invasion of Ukraine\, bringing together a
 rtists\, curators\, researchers and local communities to work with archive
 s\, sites of memory and present-day social realities. WHO THEY SEEK: artis
 ts whose practice engages themes such as memory and remembrance\, identity
 \, war and its consequences\, migration and displacement\, archives and do
 cumentary practices\, the relationship between past and present\, and ecol
 ogical and social transformation\, working across visual arts\, photograph
 y\, film and video\, sound art\, illustration\, graphic storytelling\, pod
 casts and audio\, or interdisciplinary practice. No age restrictions. ELIG
 IBILITY: artists based in countries participating in Creative Europe (EU m
 ember states\; Iceland\, Norway\, Liechtenstein\; and accession/candidate/
 potential-candidate countries including Albania\, Bosnia and Herzegovina\,
  Georgia\, Kosovo\, Montenegro\, North Macedonia\, Serbia\, Ukraine\, Arme
 nia and Tunisia). STRUCTURE: an international jury selects 15 participants
  for three research and workshop programmes (Bosnia and Herzegovina Jul/Au
 g 2026\, Italy Oct 2026\, Ukraine online)\; 6 artists are then selected to
  continue into the 2027 residency programme (on-site in Italy and Bosnia a
 nd Herzegovina\, plus an online residency connected to Ukraine with The 4t
 h Block)\, with outcomes shown in international exhibitions in the partner
  countries (the Ukrainian exhibition in a safe location in Lviv) and the T
 RACE digital archive. WHAT PARTICIPANTS RECEIVE: coverage of travel\, acco
 mmodation and meals during programme activities (up to Creative Europe lim
 its)\, international visibility and PR support\, access to archives and co
 mmunities\, mentorship\, professional documentation and a certificate\; th
 ere is NO daily artist fee and no production equipment. English is the wor
 king language. APPLY via the Google Form with a portfolio (max 5MB PDF) or
  website\, a short project proposal/research idea (max 1 page) and a short
  biography. Deadline: 18 June 2026 (Rome time\, UTC+2)\; selected particip
 ants contacted by 28 June. Questions: info@tracearts.eu.\n\nOrganisation: 
 Camera a Sud (Italy)\, Forgotten Children of War Association (Bosnia and H
 erzegovina) and The 4th Block (Ukraine)\nLocation: Italy\, Bosnia and Herz
 egovina\, and online (Ukraine)\; open to artists based in Creative Europe 
 programme countries.\nAward: NO daily artist fee. Travel\, accommodation a
 nd meals covered during programme activities (up to the maximum allowed un
 der Creative Europe regulations). Technical equipment for producing artwor
 ks is NOT provided. Plus international visibility/PR\, exhibitions\, mento
 rship and a certificate. No application fee.\nDuration: Research missions 
 in 2026 (Bosnia and Herzegovina Jul/Aug\, Italy Oct\, Ukraine online)\; re
 sidencies in 2027 for 6 selected artists\n\nMore: https://docs.google.com/
 forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdWVCzfj9fSe_WprayCTcAIucx58JluguVv1dP-x6WlOvCT1Q/viewfor
 m?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdWVCzfj9fSe_WprayCTcAIucx58Jl
 uguVv1dP-x6WlOvCT1Q/viewform?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_med
 ium=referral
LOCATION:Italy\, Bosnia and Herzegovina\, and online (Ukraine)\; open to ar
 tists based in Creative Europe programme countries.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:emap-emare-media-art-residencies-2027@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T221418Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261106
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261107
SUMMARY:Deadline: EMAP / EMARE: European Media Art Platform Residencies 202
 7
DESCRIPTION:The European Media Art Platform (EMAP/EMARE) is a network of le
 ading European media-art organisations offering fully funded two-month pro
 duction residencies for artists working with digital media\, including med
 ia art\, bio art and robotic art. Each residency provides a EUR 4\,000 gra
 nt to the applying artist (including subsistence)\, a EUR 4\,000 project b
 udget\, host-provided accommodation\, travel covered according to EU ceili
 ngs\, and access to technical facilities and media labs\; a collaborating 
 artist receives an additional EUR 2\,000 (EUR 6\,000 total for a duo). Res
 idencies take place at one of 15 host institutions across Austria\, France
 \, Slovakia\, Portugal\, Belgium\, the Netherlands\, Slovenia\, Croatia\, 
 Spain\, Italy\, Cyprus\, Greece\, Latvia\, Germany and Poland. ELIGIBILITY
 : applicants must be EU residents or taxpayers in an EU member state\, or 
 residents/taxpayers of one of the eligible non-EU countries (Netherlands-b
 ased artists qualify). Undergraduate and Master's students are not eligibl
 e\; PhD candidates and emerging artists of any age and academic background
  may apply. IMPORTANT: applicants must apply as a duo or collective\, or p
 ropose a collaborative project\, rather than as a purely solo applicant. T
 he 2027 open call runs from 3 September 2026 to 6 November 2026 at 14:00 C
 ET. Apply online at call.emare.eu. No application fee.\n\nOrganisation: Eu
 ropean Media Art Platform (EMAP / EMARE)\nLocation: Two-month production r
 esidency at one of 15 host institutions across Austria\, France\, Slovakia
 \, Portugal\, Belgium\, Netherlands\, Slovenia\, Croatia\, Spain\, Italy\,
  Cyprus\, Greece\, Latvia\, Germany and Poland\nAward: EUR 4\,000 grant fo
 r the applying artist (including subsistence)\; EUR 2\,000 for a collabora
 ting artist (EUR 6\,000 total for a duo)\; EUR 4\,000 project budget\; acc
 ommodation provided by the host\; travel covered per EU ceilings\; access 
 to technical facilities and media labs. No application fee.\nDuration: Two
  months\n\nMore: https://emare.eu/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&u
 tm_medium=referral
URL:https://emare.eu/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=refe
 rral
LOCATION:Two-month production residency at one of 15 host institutions acro
 ss Austria\, France\, Slovakia\, Portugal\, Belgium\, Netherlands\, Sloven
 ia\, Croatia\, Spain\, Italy\, Cyprus\, Greece\, Latvia\, Germany and Pola
 nd
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
